seed_metadata
  bucket "wiktionary-pages"
  format "Links Notation; one `response_<short_id>` record per fetched URL"
  populated_by "examples/refresh_translation_cache.rs"
  max_records "256"
  max_lines "1500"
  split_marker "wiktionary-pages-partN.lino"
  body_format "raw response text; concatenate `body` chunks; values escape one literal quote as two consecutive quotes per Links Notation"
response_0000_api_php_action_parse_pag
  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=%29&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":"")"",""pageid"":79118,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""{{also|\\:)|( )|◌᪻|◌᪽}}\n{{character info}}\n{{character info/var|⁾|₎|⎞|⎟|⎠|︶|﹚|）|｠|⦆}}\n==Translingual==\n\n===Punctuation mark===\n{{m"
  body "ul-punctuation mark}}\n\n# {{n-g|Represents a [[mouth]] vertically [[align]]ed, in order to form emoticons.}}\n# {{senseid|mul|list separator}} {{n-g|Separates a [[letter]] or [[number]] from an item "
  body "in a list.}}\n#: {{syn|mul|.<id:list separator>}}\n#: {{nsyn|mul|( )}}\n#: ''A''')''' New York, B''')''' London, C''')''' Paris.''\n#: ''a''')''' New York, b''')''' London, c''')''' Paris.''\n#: ''1''"
  body "')''' New York, 2''')''' London, 3''')''' Paris.''\n#: ''I''')''' New York, II''')''' London, III''')''' Paris.''\n#* {{quote-journal|en|termlang=mul|date=2024-09-21|author=Heath Owens|title=What to W"
  body "ear to Sabrina Carpenter's 'Short N' Sweet' Tour|journal=w:[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/style-beauty/fashion/a62289922/what-to-wear-to-sabrina-carpenter-co"
  body "ncert-short-n-sweet-tour/|passage=Whether a specific moment in pop culture history—i.e. {{w|Madonna}} at the VMAs—or a callback to an iconic style decade—her '70s curtain bangs or '50s-style swimwear "
  body "from the \""{{w|Espresso (song)|Espresso}}\"" music video—these looks are A''')''' easy to recreate and B''')''' ''so'' wearable for repeated use after your tour date has come and gone.}}\n# {{ng|Used i"
  body "n {{m|mul|( )}}.}}\n#* {{quote-web|en|termlang=mul|title=Can AI Change Your View? Evidence from a Large-Scale Online Field Experiment|url=https://retractionwatch.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Extende"
  body "dAbstract-Zurich-AI-Reddit.pdf|date=2025-04|page=1|work=w:University of Zurich|passage=Large Language Models (LLMs''')''' are fundamentally transforming how humans consume and interact with informatio"
  body "n, raising pressing ethical concerns about their broader societal impact.}}\n\n====Quotations====\n{{see citations|mul|(}}\n\n===Symbol===\n{{mul-symbol}}\n\n# {{lb|mul|mathematics}} {{ng|Denotes an o"
  body "pen endpoint of an {{w|Interval (mathematics)|interval}}.}}\n#: <math>[a,b)=\\{x\\in\\R\\,|\\,a\\le x<b\\}</math>\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|mul|[}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|jbo|toi}} (Lojban)\n{{pu"
  body "nctuation}}\n\n==Azerbaijani==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|az|ru|)}}.\n\n===Punctuation mark===\n{{head|az|punctuation mark}}\n\n# {{lb|az|Internet slang|text messaging}} {{l|mul|\\:-)}}, expressing ha"
  body "ppiness or amusement.\n\n====Usage notes====\nThe methods in using '')'' as an Internet slang expression in Azerbaijani are similar to that in Russian and Ukrainian.\n\nGenerally, the number of bracke"
  body "ts may vary, but it can also be just one bracket at the end of a sentence.\n\n==Chinese==\n\n===Punctuation mark===\n{{head|zh|punctuation mark}}\n\n# {{n-g|used in {{l|zh|( )}}}}\n\n==Japanese==\n\n="
  body "==Punctuation mark===\n{{head|ja|punctuation mark}}\n\n# Used in {{l|ja|( )}}.\n\n==Russian==\n\n===Etymology===\nEvolved from {{l|mul|\\:-)}}. In the {{w|JCUKEN|Russian keyboard layout}}, one has to "
  body "press Shift+6 to type a colon, which is deemed inconvenient, particularly in instant messaging, as it requires both hands, resulting in the decline of {{l|mul|\\:-)}}.\n\n===Punctuation mark===\n{{hea"
  body "d|ru|punctuation mark}}\n\n# {{lb|ru|Internet slang|text messaging}} {{l|mul|\\:-)}}, expressing happiness or amusement.\n\n====Usage notes====\nUsage of multiple brackets is used to emphasize the lau"
  body "ghter or humor, but it may also suggest an ironic or sarcastic tone. \nMultiple brackets with zeroes - )0 or (9 - are used similarly to [[!1]], implying that shift key was released, expressing an emph"
  body "asis.\n\"")))\"" is not to be confused with [[((( )))]], known as a far-right symbol directed against Jewish people.\n\n====Antonyms====\n* {{l|ru|(}} (online slang, expression of sadness or disappointm"
  body "ent)\n\n====Related terms====\n* [[)))#Russian|)))]] (online slang, expression of laughter)\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|az|)|bor=1}}""}}"

