response_0008_api_php_action_parse_pag
  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=bread&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""bread"",""pageid"":7381,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""==English==\n{{wp}}\n{{wikibooks|cookbook=bread}}\n[[File:Serbian bread.jpg|thumb|Two [[loaf|loaves]] of bread (1).]]\n\n===Pronuncia"
  body "tion===\n* {{IPA|en|/brɛd/|/brɛːd/|a=Early Modern}}<ref>{{R:en:Dobson:1957|II|30|502}}</ref>\n* {{enPR|brĕd|a=RP,GA,CA}}, {{IPA|en|/bɹɛd/}}\n* {{audio|en|En-uk-bread.ogg|a=RP}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 "
  body "(eng)-Naomi Persephone Amethyst (NaomiAmethyst)-bread.wav|a=GA}}\n* {{audio|en|En-us-bread.ogg|a=GA}}\n* {{IPA|en|/bɹed/|a=AU,NZ}}\n* {{homophones|en|bred}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɛd|s=1}}\n\n===Etymology 1=="
  body "=\n{{etymon|en|id=food|:inh|enm:bred|tree=1}}\n{{root|en|ine-pro|*bʰrewh₁-}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|bred}}, {{m|enm|breed}}, from {{inh|en|ang|brēad|t=fragment, bit, morsel, crumb\"", also \""bread}}, from "
  body "{{inh|en|gmw-pro|*braud}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*braudą|t=bread}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*bʰrewh₁-|*bʰerw-, *bʰrewh₁-|t=to boil; to brew}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*bʰer-|t=to bear, carry}}. Alternatively, "
  body "from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*braudaz}}, {{m|gem-pro|*brauþaz|t=broken piece, fragment}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*bʰera-|t=to split, beat, hew, struggle}} (see {{l|en|brittle}}). Perhaps a conflation of the t"
  body "wo. Possibly a {{doublet|en|broa|nocap=1}}. \n{{col-top|2|cog}}\nCognate with {{cog|sco|breid|t=bread}}, {{cog|yol|breed|t=bread}}, {{cog|frr|bruad}}, {{m|frr|Bruar}}, {{m|frr|brüüdj|t=bread}}, {{cog|"
  body "stq|Brood|t=bread}}, {{cog|fy|brea|t=bread}}, {{cog|gsw|brot}}, {{m|gsw|broud}}, {{m|gsw|bruat}}, {{m|gsw|bròt}}, {{m|gsw|bröt|t=bread}}, {{cog|cim|proat}}, {{m|cim|pròat|t=bread}}, {{cog|nl|brood|t=b"
  body "read}}, {{cog|de|Brot|t=bread}}, {{cog|nds-de|Brod}}, {{m|nds-de|Brood}}, {{m|nds-de|Broot}}, {{m|nds-de|Brot}}, {{m|nds-de|Bräot|t=bread}}, {{cog|li|broed|t=bread}}, {{cog|lb|Brout|t=bread}}, {{cog|m"
  body "hn|proat|t=bread}}, {{cog|wym|brūt|t=bread; loaf}}, {{cog|yi|ברויט|t=bread}}, {{cog|da,nb|brød|t=bread}}, {{cog|ovd|broð|t=bread}}, {{cog|fo| breyð|t=bread}}, {{cog|is|brauð|t=bread}}, {{cog|nrn|brau}"
  body "}, {{m|nrn|brow|t=bread}}, {{cog|nn|braud}}, {{m|nn|brød|t=bread}}, {{cog|sv|bröd|t=bread}}, {{cog|gme-cgo|broe|t=bread}}; also {{cog|kw|brys|t=thought; mind}}, {{cog|ga,gd|beir|t=bear, give birth to}"
  body "}, {{cog|cy|bryd|t=aim, intent}}, {{cog|la|fors|t=chance, luck}}, {{cog|el|φέρνω}}, {{m|el|φέρω|t=to bear, carry}}, {{cog|sq|brydh|t=to ripen, soften; to crumble}}, {{cog|lv|bērt|t=to pour; to scatter"
  body ", strew}}, {{cog|lt|berti|t=to scatter, strew}}, {{cog|be|бру́ха|t=belly}}, {{cog|cs|břich}}, {{m|cs|břicho}}, {{m|cs|břuch|t=belly}}, {{cog|csb|brzëch|t=belly}}, {{cog|pl|brzuch}}, {{m|pl|brzucho|t=b"
  body "elly}}, {{cog|ru|брю́хо|t=belly}}, {{cog|sk|brucho|t=belly}}, {{cog|hy|բերել|t=to bring, fetch}}, {{cog|fa|بردن|tr=bordan/burdan|t=to bear, carry}}, {{cog|xto,txb|pär-|t=to bear; to wear}}, {{cog|sa|भ"
  body "ारयति|t=to carry}}. \n{{col-bottom}}\nEclipsed non-native {{noncog|enm|payn|t=bread}}, borrowed from {{noncog|fro|pain|t=bread}}. In this sense, mostly replaced {{m|en|loaf}}, which had been the more "
  body "common term in Old English (see {{m|ang|hlaf}}), a process which similarly occured in other languages such as German.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alter|en|breade||obsolete}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{e"
  body "n-noun|~}}\n\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}}\n## {{senseid|en|Q7802}} A [[foodstuff]] made by [[bake|baking]] [[dough]] made from [[cereal]]s.\n##: {{hypo|en|tack<id:food, especially bread or breadlike food>"
  body "|biscuit<id:durable, hard, dry bread or breadlike foodstuff>}}\n### {{lb|en|especially}} Such foodstuff that is not difficult to [[chew#Verb|chew]], being not extremely hard, dense, and dry.\n###: {{c"
  body "ot|en|tack<id:food, especially bread or breadlike food>|biscuit<id:durable, hard, dry bread or breadlike foodstuff>}}\n###: {{ux|en|We made sandwiches with the '''bread''' we bought from the bakery.}}"
  body "\n###: {{ux|en|My mother used to send me for the '''bread'''.}}\n###* {{RQ:Lincoln Pratt's Patients|chapter=8|passage=Philander went into the next room{{...}}and came back with a salt mackerel that dr"
  body "ipped brine like a rainstorm. Then he put the coffee pot on the stove and rummaged out a loaf of dry '''bread''' and some hardtack.}}\n## Food; sustenance; support of life, in general.\n##: {{syn|en|s"
  body "taff of life}}\n##* {{RQ:KJV|Matthew|4|11||Give us this day our daily '''bread'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|countable}} Any variety of bread.\n#: {{ux|en|Some '''breads''' are harder and drier than others.}}\n# {"
  body "{senseid|en|money}} {{lb|en|slang|US|or|Cockney}} [[money|Money]].\n#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:money}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1962|year_published=1963|month_published=January|author=w:James Baldwin|title"
  body "={{w|Another Country (novel)|Another Country}}|location=New York, N. Y.|publisher=w:The Dial Press|pages=3–4|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/anothercountry0000bald/page/4/mode/2up?q=bread|passage="
  body "Maybe somebody would see him and recognize him, maybe one of the guys would lay enough '''bread''' on him for a meal or at least subway fare.}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|year=1967|artist=w:Eric Burdon; w:Th"
  body "e Animals|album=Winds of Change|title=w:San Franciscan Nights|passage={{...|This is a very personal song, so if the viewer cannot understand it, particularly those of you who are European residents,}}"
  body " save up all your '''bread''', and fly Trans-Love Airways to San Francisco, USA.}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|year=1973|composer=w:Billy Joel|author=w:Billy Joel|artist=w:Billy Joel|title=[[w:Piano Man (song"
  body ")|Piano Man]]|passage=And they sit at the bar and put '''bread''' in my jar / And say, \""Man, what are you doing here?\""}}\n#* {{quote-av|en|title=w:Requiem for a Dream|writer=w:Darren Aronofsky; w:Hu"
  body "bert Selby Jr.|year=2000|passage=Hey, baby, I don't care if the motherfucker's growing hair just so long as we get our '''bread'''.|role=Tyrone}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|lyricist=Jordan Houston; Darnell C"
  body "arlton; Paul Beauregard; Premro Smith; Marlon Goodwin; David Brown; Willie Hutchinson|passage=Tastes like fruit when you hit it; got to have '''bread''' to get it.|url=https://genius.com/Three-6-mafia"
