  body "}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|ac eithrio}}\n* Zazaki: {{t+|zza|la}}, {{t|zza|nara}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|solely, only, merely (obsolete)}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|ancaq}}, {{t|az|təkcə}}\n* Chechen:"
  body " {{t|ce|бен}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|只|tr=zhǐ}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|que}}, {{t+|fr|seulement}}\n* Galician: {{t|gl|somente}}, {{t|gl|namais}}, {{t|gl|xiquera}}\n* German: {{t+|de|nur}}\n* H"
  body "ungarian: {{t+|hu|csak}}, {{t+|hu|csupán}}, {{t+|hu|mindössze}}, {{t+|hu|pusztán}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|だけ|tr=dake}}, {{t+|ja|しか|tr=shika}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t+|lt|tik}}, {{t+|lt|vos}}\n* Old English: "
  body "{{t|ang|būtan}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|doar}}, {{t+|ro|numai}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|то́лько}}, {{t+|ru|лишь}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|len}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|sólo}}, {{t+|es|solamente}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|بس|tr"
  body "=bas}}\n* Zazaki: {{t|zza|teyna}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Arabic: {{t+check|ar|بَل}}\n* Greek:\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t-check|grc|ἀλλά}}\n* Hungarian: {{t-check|hu|[[kivéve]] [[-t]], "
  body "[[csak]]}} (after a negative sentence), {{t-check|hu|[[csak]] [[nem]]}} (after a positive sentence)\n* Indonesian: {{t+check|id|tapi}}, {{t+check|id|tetapi}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+chec"
  body "k|kmr|lê}} {{q|Kurmanji}}\n* Old Prussian: {{t-check|prg|aber}}\n* Persian:\n*: Iranian Persian: {{t-check|fa-ira|وَلی}}\n* Tamil: {{t+check|ta|ஆனால்}}\n* Telugu: {{t+check|te|కానీ}}\n* Volapük: {{t+c"
  body "heck|vo|ab}}, {{t+check|vo|efe}}, {{t+check|vo|sod}} (archaic)\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# An [[instance#Noun|instance]] of using the word \""but\""; an [[objection#Noun|objection]"
  body "] or [[caveat#Noun|caveat]].\n#: {{ux|en|It has to be done—no ifs, ands, or '''buts'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|But—and this is a big '''but'''—you have to come home by sundown.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=19"
  body "22-03-04|title=Fed on Fear Too Much|journal=The Pathfinder|location=Washington, D.C.|publisher=Pathfinder Publishing Company|volume=29|issue=1470|page=33|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/sim_town-j"
  body "ournal_1922-03-04_29_1470/page/32/mode/2up?q=%22buts+and+nots%22|passage=The children are taught to be afraid of winter, of war, of death, of hard times, of disease, of examtinations. Perhaps that is "
  body "one of the reasons that children so seldom find the conversation of their elders uplifting. It is full of don’ts, '''buts''' and nots.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Concepcion de Leon|title=5 Things"
  body " Well-Meaning People Say to Me That Are Actually Really Offensive|work=[[w:Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20230208093938/https://www.glamour.com/story/5-things-wel"
  body "l-meaning-people-say-to-me-that-are-actually-really-offensive|location=Greenwich, C.T.;{{nb...|New York, N.Y.; Los Angeles, C.A.}}|publisher=[[w:Condé Nast|Condé Nast Publications]]|date=28 December 2"
  body "016|issn=0017-0747|oclc=5259082|passage=\""I support you/understand where you're coming from, but...\"" ¶ No. No \""'''buts'''\"" when it comes to other people's survival.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author="
  body "Catriona Harvey-Jenner|title=8 foods you should never eat before a workout|work=[[w:Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20230128234014/https://www.cosmopolita"
  body "n.com/uk/body/diet-nutrition/a23280061/foods-never-eat-before-workout/|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=w:Hearst Communications|date=17 September 2018|issn=0010-9541|oclc=1770745|passage=But - and th"
  body "is is a pretty important '''but''' - it's just as bad to eat the ''wrong'' thing before a workout as it is to eat nothing at all.}}\n# {{lb|en|Scotland}} The [[outer]] [[room]] of a small two-room [[c"
  body "ottage]].\n# A [[limit]]; a [[boundary]].\n# The end; especially the larger or thicker end, or the blunt, in distinction from the sharp, end; the [[butt]].\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|top and b"
  body "ut}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb|++}}\n\n# {{lb|en|archaic}} Use the word \""but\"".\n#: {{ux|en|'''But''' me no buts.}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col3|en|title=Terms derived from the preposition, adverb"
  body ", conjunction, or noun ''but''|all but|but and ben|but good|ifs, ands, or buts|but that|can but hope|all-but|anything but|but for|but for the grace of God|but hey|but if|but me no buts|but seriously f"
  body "olks|but then|but then again|but who's counting|cannot but|cannot help but|gurry-but|not but|not only … but also|nothing but|though but|can't but|can't help but|everything but the galley stove|it's no"
  body "t what you know but whom you know|it's not what you say but how you say it|Jill of all trades but mistress of none|silent-but-violent|yesterday but one}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n* {{R:Ce"
  body "ntury 1911}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=btu|BTU|TBU|tub}}\n\n{{cln|en|coordinating conjunctions|focus adverbs|3-letter words}}\n\n==Cornish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|kw|en|butt}}.\n\n===N"
  body "oun===\n{{kw-noun|m|ys}}\n\n# {{lb|kw|archery}} {{l|en|butt}}\n\n===Mutation===\n{{kw-mut}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:CDGK}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|da|gml|butt}}.\n\n===Adjectiv"
  body "e===\n{{da-adj}}\n\n# {{lb|da|rare}} [[blunt]]\n\n====Inflection====\n{{da-infl-adj|butt}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|da|stump}}\n\n====Antonyms====\n* {{l|da|spids}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology 1=="
  body "=\nFrom {{der|fr|frm|but||mark, goal}}, from {{der|fr|fro|but||aim, goal, end, target}}, from {{der|fr|fro|butte||mound, knoll, target}}, from {{der|fr|frk|*but||stump, log}}, or from {{der|fr|non|bút"
  body "r||log, stump, butt}}; both from {{der|fr|gem-pro|*buttaz||end, piece}}.\n\nCognate with {{cog|ang|butt||tree stump}}; see {{m|en|butt}}. The semantic development from \""mound\"" to \""target\"" is likel"
  body "y from [[martial]] training practice. The final {{IPAchar|/t/}} is from the old pausal and liaison pronunciation; its (partial) restoration as the basic form may have been reinforced by related {{m|fr"
  body "|butte}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{fr-IPA|butt|a=outside Canada now more often}}\n** {{homophones|fr|bute|butent|butes|bûtes|buts|butte|buttent|buttes}}\n** {{audio|fr|Fr-but.ogg}}\n\n====Noun==="
  body "=\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# [[aim]]\n# [[goal]] {{gloss|result one is attempting to achieve}}\n# {{lb|fr|sports}} [[goal]] {{gloss|in the place, act, or point sense}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{l|fr|fin}}\n"
  body "* {{l|fr|objectif}}\n* {{l|fr|dessein}}\n* {{l|fr|point}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col3|fr\n|but cadré\n|but contre son camp\n|but en argent\n|but en or\n|buter\n|buteur\n|buteuse\n|coup de pied "
  body "de but\n|de but en blanc\n|deuxième but\n|droit au but\n|gardien de but\n|gardienne de but\n|premier but\n|tirs au but\n|troisième but\n}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{m|fr|boire}}.\n\n====Pronunciati"
  body "on====\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{homophones|fr|bu|bue|bues|bus|bût|buts}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|fr|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|fr|boire||3|s|phis}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n{{C|fr|"
  body "Football (soccer)|Handball|Hockey}}\n{{cln|fr|terms with irregularly sounded consonant}}\n\n==Iban==\n\n===Adjective===\n{{head|iba|adjective}}\n\n# [[stinky]]\n\n==Indonesian==\n\n===Noun===\n{{id-no"
  body "un}}\n\n# {{lb|id|computing}} [[bootstrap]] (process by which the operating system of a computer is loaded into its memory)\n\n===References===\n* {{R:KBBI Daring}}\n\n==Maltese==\n{{mt-root|b-w-t}}\n"
  body "\n===Etymology===\nProbably from {{inh|mt|ar|بُوطَة}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|mt|/buːt/}}\n* {{rhymes|mt|uːt|s=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{mt-noun|g=m|p=bwiet|dim=bwejjet|dim2=buta|dim3=bwejta}}\n\n"
  body "# [[pocket]]\n# {{lb|mt|figuratively}} [[money]]\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|enm|ang|būtan}}, from {{inh|enm|gmw-pro|*biūtan}}, {{m|gmw-pro|*biūtini}}, equivalent to {{af|en"
  body "m|be-|out|nocat=1}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alter|enm|bute|buten|boute|bouten}}\n* {{alter|enm|botte|bot|bod}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|enm|/but/}}\n\n====Conjunction====\n{{head|e"
  body "nm|conjunction}}\n\n# {{l|en|but}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|en|but}}\n* {{desc|sco|but}}\n* {{desc|yol|mot}}\n\n=====References=====\n* {{R:MED Online|entry=but|pos=conj|id=MED6406}}\n\n===E"
  body "tymology 2===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}}\n\n# {{tlb|enm|Northern ME}} {{alt form|enm|bote|t=boot|id=boot}}\n\n[[Category:Northern Middle English]]\n\n==Old Polish==\n\n===Pronunciati"
  body "on===\n* {{zlw-opl-IPA}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{zlw-opl-noun|m-in}}\n\n# {{alt form|zlw-opl|bot}}\n\n==Polish==\n{{wp|pl:}}\n[[File:Black Converse sneakers.JPG|thumb|buty]]\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{a"
  body "lt|pl|bot||Middle Polish}}\n* {{alt|pl|bót||obsolete|or|dialectal|Lubawa}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|pl|id=shoe|:inh|zlw-opl:bot<id:shoe>|tree=1}}\n{{inh+|pl|zlw-opl|bot}}, which see for more on th"
  body "e change in the vowel.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|a=Pl-but.ogg;LL-Q809 (pol)-Olaf-but.wav|hh=bud|mp=#|suw=#|CD=#}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|m-in,m-anml|dim=bucik,butek|aug=bucior,bucisko}}\n\n# ["
  body "[shoe]]\n## [[boot]] {{gl|heavy shoe that covers part of the leg}}\n# {{lb|pl|Chełmno|unit of measure}} {{syn of|pl|stopa}}\n# {{lb|pl|construction|sailing}} [[keel]] [[block]] {{gl|wooden base on whi"
  body "ch the support that holds the ship's hull during rests for construction}}\n# [[pile shoe]] {{gl|metal tip to a pole that is to be driven into the ground}}\n# {{lb|pl|Chełmno|Suwałki|unit of measure}} "
  body "{{syn of|pl|stopa}}\n# {{lb|pl|obsolete|jocular|in the plural}} [[seventy seven]] {{gl|the number 77 is a game of chance}}\n# {{lb|pl|Middle Polish}} [[boot]] {{gl|horse leg protector, worn for therap"
  body "eutic purposes}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{pl-decl-noun-m-anml|accs=but/buta}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|pl|title=adverbs|pod butem|z buta}}\n{{col|pl|title=interjections|takie buty}}\n{{col|pl|t"
  body "itle=nouns|czyścibut|łyżka do butów|pucybut|półbut|siedmiomilowe buty}}\n{{col|pl|title=particles|}}\n{{col|pl|title=phrases|buty pospadały|buty z nóg spadają|słoma z butów wystaje|umarł w butach}}\n{"
  body "{col|pl|title=prepositions|pod butem}}\n{{col|pl|title=proverbs|idzie luty, podkuj buty|szewc bez butów chodzi|trza być w butach na weselu}}\n{{pl-derived verbs\n|wyrwać z butów/wyrywać z butów\n|-/ki"
  body "wać palcem w bucie\n|uszyć buty/szyć buty\n|wejść w buty/wchodzić w buty\n|wejść z butami/wchodzić z butami}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:WSJP||1971}}\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n* {{R:pl:SXVI|+|44644}}\n"
  body "* {{R:pl:SXVII|BUT|8122||28.04.2010}}\n* {{R:pl:SJP1807}}\n* {{R:pl:SJP1861}}\n* {{R:pl:SJP1900||240|1}}\n* {{R:pl:SGP1900||143|1}}\n* {{R:pl:NFJP}}\n* {{R:pl:Nitsch:1907||387}}\n\n{{C|pl|Footwear|Uni"
  body "ts of measure}}\n\n==Romani==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{inh+|rom|pra-sau|𑀩𑀳𑀼𑀢𑁆𑀢}},<ref name=\""bi\"">{{R:rom:Boretzky-Igla|but|page=39b}}</ref> from {{inh|rom|sa|बहुत्व|t=much, many, very}}.<ref name=\""bi\"""
  body "/><ref name=\""t\"">{{R:CDIAL|bahutva|9190|page=519}}</ref> Cognate with {{cog|hi|बहुत}}.\n\n===Adjective===\n{{head|rom|adjective|oblique|bute|cat2=1-syllable words}}\n\n# [[much]]<ref name=\""bi\""/><re"
  body "f name=\""t\""/><ref name=\""cI\"">{{R:Courthiade:2009|entry=but B-ćham: -e I|page=97a}}</ref><ref name=\""s\"">{{R:NERG+|entry=but|page=147}}</ref>\n# [[many]]<ref name=\""bi\""/><ref name=\""t\""/><ref name=\"""
  body "cI\""/>\n#: {{ux|rom|'''But''' rroma mekhle i India thaj gele p-e aver phuva.''|t='''Many''' Roma left India and went towards other lands.}}\n\n===Adverb===\n{{head|rom|adverb}}\n\n# [[very]]<ref name="
  body "\""bi\""/><ref name=\""s\""/><ref>{{R:Courthiade:2009|entry=but II|page=97a}}</ref>\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|ro|ota|بوت|tr=but}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{ro-n"
  body "oun|n|buturi}}\n\n# [[thigh]] of an animal\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-noun-n-uri}}\n\n==Scots==\n\n===Noun===\n{{sco-noun}}\n\n# The [[outer]] [[room]] of a small two-room [[cottage]].\n\n===Preposit"
  body "ion===\n{{h|sco|prep}}\n\n# [[outside|Outside]] of, [[without]].\n\n==Serbo-Croatian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|sh|ota|بوت|tr=but}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sh|/bût/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sh-no"
  body "un|bȕt|m-in}}\n\n# [[thigh]]\n# [[ham]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{sh-decl-noun\n|bȕt|bùtovi\n|bùta|butova\n|butu|butovima\n|but|butove\n|bute|butovi\n|butu|butovima\n|butom|butovima\n}}\n\n===Reference"
  body "s===\n* {{R:sh:HJP|f11kURA%3D}}\n\n==Turkish==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|tr|bud||dialectal}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|tr|ota|بود|tr=bud}}, {{m|ota|بوت|tr=but}}, from {{inh|tr|trk-pro"
  body "|*būt}}. Compare {{cog|otk|tr=būt}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|tr|LL-Q256 (tur)-ToprakM-but.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{tr-noun|u|lar}}\n\n# [[thigh]]\n#: {{syn|tr|uyluk}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{"
  body "tr-infl-noun-c|u|poss=1}}\n\n==Volapük==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|vo|/but/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{vo-noun}}\n\n# [[boot]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{vo-decl-noun}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:vo:"
  body "Vödabuk}}\n\n{{C|vo|Footwear}}""}}"

response_0010_api_php_action_parse_pag
  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=carrot&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""carrot"",""pageid"":41969,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""==English==\n{{wp}}\n{{wikispecies|Daucus carota}}\n[[Image:Carrot.jpg|thumb|Carrots]]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|en|qsb-grc}}\nF"
  body "rom {{inh|en|enm|karette}} and {{bor|en|frm|carotte}}, both from {{der|en|la|carōta}}, from {{der|en|grc|καρωτόν}}. {{doublet|en|carotte}} and related to {{m|en|caraway}}. Displaced native {{ncog|enm|"
  body "more}}, from {{ncog|ang|more}}, {{m|ang|moru|t=edible root, parsnip, carrot}}, related to {{ncog|de|Möhre|t=carrot}}.\n* Noun sense of \""motivational tool\"" refers to {{m|en|carrot and stick}}.\n* Ver"
  body "b sense in felt manufacture refers to the orange colour of drying furs.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|kâr'ət|a=RP}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈkæɹət/}}\n* {{enPR|kâr'ət|a=GenAm,nMmmm}} {{IPA|en|/ˈkæɹət/}}\n** {{a"
  body "udio|en|en-us-ne-carrot.ogg|a=US,nMmmm}}\n* {{enPR|kĕr'ət|a=GenAm,Mmmm}} {{IPA|en|/ˈkɛɹət/}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-carrot.ogg|a=US,Mmmm}}\n* {{rhymes|en|æɹət|s=2}}\n* {{homophones|en|carat|karat}}\n* {"
  body "{homophones|en|caret|aa=weak vowel}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|car|rot}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q81}}A [[vegetable]] with a [[nutritious]], [[juicy]], [[sweet]] [[root]] that is ofte"
  body "n [[orange]] in colour, {{taxfmt|Daucus carota|species}}, family {{taxfmt|Apiaceae|family}}, especially the subspecies ''sativus''.\n#: {{syn|en|more<id:carrot><q:obsolete>}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year="
  body "1961|author=Harry E. Wedeck|title=Dictionary of Aphrodisiacs|publisher=The Citadel Press|location=New York|page=42|passage=In general, beets, '''carrots''', and turnips are all of aphrodisiac value in"
  body " erotic dietary.}}\n# A shade of orange similar to the [[flesh]] of most carrots (also called carrot orange).\n#: {{color panel|ED9121}}\n# {{senseid|en|incentive}} {{lb|en|figurative}} Any [[motivati"
  body "onal]] tool; an [[incentive]] to do something.\n#: {{cot|en|stick<id:punishment>}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Coral Davenport; Lisa Friedman|title=Five Decades in the Making: Why It Took Congress S"
  body "o Long to Act on Climate|work=The New York Times|date=2022-08-07|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2022/08/07/climate/senate-climate-law.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=Essentially, lawmakers replaced the stick"
  body "s with '''carrots'''.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Paul Krugman|title=Climate Is Now a Culture War Issue|date=2023-08-07|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2023/08/07/opinion/climate-is-now-a-culture-war-"
  body "issue.html|work=The New York Times|passage=In 2022, when the Biden administration finally succeeded in passing a major climate bill, it consisted almost entirely of '''carrots'''—tax credits and subsi"
  body "dies for green energy.}}\n# {{lb|en|UK|slang|derogatory}} Someone from a [[rural]] background.\n# {{lb|en|UK|slang}} A police officer from somewhere within the British Isles, but specifically outside "
  body "of Greater London.\n# {{lb|en|slang}} A [[redhead]]; a [[ginger]]-haired person\n# {{rfdef|en}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|year=2025|author={{w|Ghostface Killah}}|title=Metaphysics|text=I got the jammy loade"
  body "d in one hand.<br>Threw a few shots at two '''carrots''' and one jam}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en| white carrot|cuff the carrot|carrot beetle\n|carotane |carotene |carroter |carrotish |carrotw"
  body "ood |rainbow carrots |baby carrot |Camberwell carrot |carrot and stick |carrot bag |carrot cake |carrot cruncher |carrot top |carrotless |carrotlike |carroty |stick and carrot |baby-cut carrot |carrot"
  body " weevil |carrot-and-stick |carrot-top |carrot-topped |deadly carrot |stick-and-carrot |like peas and carrots |carrot bacon |carrot dog |carrot-nosed |moon carrot |wild carrot |cry carrots and turnips|"
  body "carrot fly|carrot rust fly\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|fj|kareti|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ms|karot|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tl|karot|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ta|கேரட்|bor=1|alts=1}}\n* {{desc|th|แครอท|bor=1}}\n\n"
  body "====Translations====\n{{multitrans|data=\n{{trans-top|''Daucus carota'' ssp. ''sativus''}}\n* Abkhaz: {{tt|ab|ажьаҷыркәа}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|wortel}}\n* Ainu: {{t|ain|フレアタネ|tr=huneatane}}\n* Alab"
