  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=cucumber&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""cucumber"",""pageid"":42228,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""==English==\n[[File:Australia_Cucumbers_for_sale_at_store.jpg|thumb|Cucumbers (2)]]\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|cuke|c"
  body "umber||both|_|colloquial}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|cucumer}}, {{m|enm|cucumber}}, from {{der|en|fro|cocombre}}, ultimately from {{der|en|la|cucumis|cucumis, cucumerem}} (possibly through"
  body " an {{der|en|pro|-}} intermediate). Probably of Pre-Italic {{der|en|qfa-sub}} origin. {{etydate|late 14c.}} Displaced native {{ncog|en|earthapple}} (see which for more), which has since acquired other"
  body " senses.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{a|en|non-rhotic}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈkjuːˌkʌmbə/|[ˈkʰjʊu̯ˌkʰʌmbə]|a=RP}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈkjuːˌkʊmbə/|[ˈkʰjʊu̯ˌkʰʊ̈mbə]|a=Northern England,non-foot-strut split}}\n* {{a|"
  body "en|rhotic}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈkjuˌkʌmbɚ/|[ˈkʰjʊu̯ˌkʰʌ̈mbɚ]|~|[ˈkʰjʊu̯ˌkʰʌ̈mbɹ̩]|a=GA}}\n*** {{audio|en|En-us-cucumber.ogg|a=US}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈkjʉˌkʌmbəɹ/|[ˈkjʉˌkʌmbəɹ]|a=Scotland}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈkaʊˌkʌ"
  body "mbəɹ/|[ˈkʰaʊ̯ˌkʰʌmbəɹ]|a=obsolete|ref2={{R:Hall PGSMS|1|10|38}} !!! {{R:en:Ross:1970|page=72}} !!! {{R:CPD|Cucumber|198|ip=1}}}}\n* {{rhyme|en|ʌmbəɹ|s=3}}\n* {{hyph|en|cu|cum|ver}}\n* {{hmp|en|Qcumber"
  body "}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# A [[vine]] in the [[gourd]] family, {{taxfmt|Cucumis sativus|species}}.\n#* {{quote-book|en|page=326|author=A Lady [Hannah Glasse]|year=1767|title=The Art of Cooke"
  body "ry Made Plain and Eaſy{{...}}|url= https://books.google.co.nz/books?id=pd5QAQAAIAAJ |passage=ASPARAGUS, cauliflowers, imperial Sileſia, royal and cabbage lettuces, burnet, purſlain, '''cucumbers''', n"
  body "aſturtian flowers, peaſe and beans ſown in October, artichokes, ſcarlet ſtrawberries, and kidney beans. }}\n# {{senseid|en|Q2735883}}The [[edible]] [[fruit]] of this [[plant]], having a [[green]] [[ri"
  body "nd]] and [[crisp]] [[white]] [[flesh]].\n#: {{syn|en|cuke|q1=informal|cumber|id2=cucumber|q2=colloquial}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1785|quotee=w:Samuel Johnson|title=Journal of a Tour to the Hebrides "
  body "with Samuel Johnſon{{...}}|author=w:James Boswell|publisher=Henry Baldwin|location=London|page=356|url=https://books.google.co.nz/books?id=E0JAAAAQAAJ|passage={{...}}for it has been a common ſaying of"
  body " phyſicians in England, that a '''cucumber''' ſhould be well ſliced, and dreſſed with pepper and vinegar, and then thrown out, as good for nothing.}}\n#* {{RQ:Landon Ethel Churchill|page=14|volume=II|"
  body "passage=\""Why, pepper and salt your reasons!\"" cried Curl, forgetting to look at the door for a moment: \""your pamphlet has talent; but talent is like a '''cucumber''', nothing without the dressing. Y"
  body "ou must be more personal.\""}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1961|author=Harry E. Wedeck|title=Dictionary of Aphrodisiacs|publisher=The Citadel Press|location=New York|page=71|passage=Probably on account of"
  body " its phallic formation, the '''cucumber''' is often assumed to have aphrodisiac qualities.}}\n#* {{RQ:NYT|date=12 March 2025|author=David Tanis|title=Cucumber-Cabbage Salad With Sesame|archiveurl=http"
  body "s://web.archive.org/web/20250313124746/https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1026666-cucumber-cabbage-salad-with-sesame|passage=To the bowl, add '''cucumber''', cabbage and carrot.}}\n# {{lb|en|informal"
  body "|figurative}} A person who is [[calm]] and [[self-possessed]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1986|title=Linking Technology and Users|author=|page=41 passage=Just a few tips will help even the most anxious "
  body "of us get a bit of control over the presentation of information and thus appear to be that \""'''cool cucumber'''\"" in cognito!}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1999|title=The Brewery |author=Mark Grantham|p"
  body "age=275|passage=The guy's a real '''cucumber'''.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2002|title=Putting on Mock Trials |author=Margaret Fisher|page=29| passage=That Wolf is one cool '''cucumber'''.}}\n#* {{quo"
  body "te-book|en|year=2018|title=American By Day|author=Derek B. Miller| page=65|passage=\""You're smart,\"" says Irv, pointing at her and nodding his head. \""A smart '''cucumber'''.\""}}\n\n====Coordinate ter"
  body "ms====\n{{col|en\n|courgette\n|gherkin\n|marrow\n|pickle\n|squash\n|zucchini\n}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|en|title=Affixed and blended forms\n|cucumberade\n|cucumber time\n|cucumber tree\n|cuc"
