  body "vìviri}}\n* Sikkimese: {{t|sip|སྐྱུར་ཉོམ}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|piti}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|beber}}, {{t+|es|tomar}}, {{t+|es|trincar}}, {{t+|es|pimplar}}, {{t+|es|chupar}}, {{t|es|drinkear}} {{qualifie"
  body "r|Chile}}, {{t+|es|trasegar}}, {{t+|es|pistear}} {{qualifier|Mexico}}, {{t+|es|escanciar}}, {{t+|es|tapinear}} {{q|Nicaragua}}\n* Swahili: {{t|sw|piga maji|alt=-piga maji}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|dricka}"
  body "}, {{t+|sv|supa}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|inom}}, {{t|tl|tagay}}, {{t+|tl|toma}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|తాగు}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|ดื่ม}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|içmek}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|[[uống]] [[rượu]]}}, {{t"
  body "|vi|[[uống]] [[say]]}}, {{t+|vi|nhậu}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|llymeitian}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|mutí}}\n* Zealandic: {{t|zea|drienke}}, {{t|zea|zupe}}\n* Zulu: {{t|zu|qhafa|alt=-qhafa}}\n}}<!-- close {{multit"
  body "rans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Breton: {{t+check|br|evañ}}\n* Guarani:\n*: Paraguayan Guarani: {{qualifier|vt}} {{t-check|gug|'u}}, {{qualifier|vi}} {{t-check|gug|y'u}}\n* Inter"
  body "lingua: {{t+check|ia|biber}}\n* Kannada: {{t+check|kn|ಕುಡಿ}}, {{t+check|kn|ಹೀರು}}\n* Khmer: {{t+check|km|ផឹក}}, {{t-check|km|ទទួលទាន}}\n* Low German: {{t+check|nds|drinken}}, {{t+check|nds|supen}}\n* "
  body "Sanskrit: {{t+check|sa|पानम्}}\n* Sinhalese: {{t-check|si|පේනා}}, {{t-check|si|පේනවා}}\n* Slovak: {{t+check|sk|piť}}\n* Tamil: {{t+check|ta|குடி}}\n* Volapük: {{t-check|vo|dlinön}}, {{t+check|vo|drinö"
  body "n}}\n* Welsh: {{t+check|cy|yfed}}\n* Woiwurrung: {{t-check|wyi|ngupa}}\n* Xhosa: {{t-check|xh|ukusela}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymon|en|id=noun|:inh|enm:drink<ety:inh<ang:drynċ>>|t"
  body "ree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|drink}}, {{m|enm|drinke}} (also as {{m|enm|drinche}}, {{m|enm|drunch}}), from {{inh|en|ang|drynċ}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*drunkiz}}, {{m|gem-pro|*drankiz}}.\n{{col-top|2|co"
  body "g}}\nCognate with {{cog|stq|Dronk|t=drink}}, {{cog|cim|gatrànkh|t=drink}}, {{cog|nl|drank}}, {{m|nl|dronk|t=drink}}, {{cog|de|Getränk}}, {{m|de|trank}}, {{m|de|Trunk|t=drink}}, {{cog|nds-de|Drank}}, {"
  body "{m|nds|Drunk|t=drink}}, {{cog|wym|gytrenḱ|t=drink}}, {{cog|da|drik|t=drink, beverage}}, {{cog|is|drykkur|t=drink, beverage}}, {{cog|nb|drikk|t=drink}}, {{cog|nn|drikk}}, {{m|nn|drykk|t=drink, alcohol}"
  body "}, {{cog|sv|dryck|t=drink}}, {{cog|got|𐌳𐍂𐌰𐌲𐌲𐌺}}, {{m|got|𐌳𐍂𐌰𐌲𐌺|t=drink}}.\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q40050}}A [[beverage]].\n#: {{ux|en|I’d like another '''drink"
  body "''' please.}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}} Drinks in general; something to drink.\n#* {{RQ:King James Version|book=Matthew|chapter=25|verse=35|passage=For I was an hungred, and ye gave me meat: I was thir"
  body "sty, and ye gave me '''drink'''}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|last=Sullivan|first=Ceri|date=6 September 2024|title=Shakespeare’s Will, Lambswool, and Puck’s Joke|journal=w:Notes and Queries|volume=71|issue"
  body "=4|page=406|publisher=w:Oxford University Press|doi=10.1093/notesj/gjae116|passage=These sources do not, however, state why the drink is called lambswool. The name comes from the way the apples are ro"
  body "asted until they split open, and their pulp froths over the skin; this is used to float on top of the bowl of '''drink'''.}}\n# A type of [[beverage]] (usually mixed).\n#: {{ux|en|My favourite '''drin"
  body "k''' is the White Russian.}}\n# {{senseid|en|Q154}} A ([[serve]]d) alcoholic [[beverage]].\n#: {{hyper|en|beverage<id:Q40050>}}\n#: {{ux|en|Can I buy you a '''drink'''?}}\n# The action of [[drinking]]"
  body ", especially with the verbs ''[[take]]'' or ''[[have]]''.\n#: {{ux|en|He was about to take a '''drink''' from his root beer.}}\n# [[alcohol|Alcoholic]] [[beverage]]s in general.\n#* {{quote-book|en|ye"
  body "ar=1935|author=[https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/288354.George_Goodchild George Goodchild]\n|title=Death on the Centre Court|chapter=1\n|passage=She mixed furniture with the same fatal profligacy"
  body " as she mixed '''drinks''', and this outrageous contact between things which were intended by Nature to be kept poles apart gave her an inexpressible thrill.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=10 Feb 79|vo"
  body "lume=6|number=28|journal=Gay Community News|page=11|title=An American Dream|author=Michael Bronski|text=By the late twenties father has died of '''drink''' and his wife is left to raise their two sons"
  body ".}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|year=1995|artist=w:Bruce McCulloch|album=Shame-Based Man|track=12|title=Daddy's on the '''Drink'''|url=https://genius.com/Bruce-mcculloch-daddys-on-the-drink-lyrics|passage=The"
  body " face of work is a drunk man in the same chair, chewing on the same bone for five thousand nights. The face of work is a, coffee cup in hand, frustrated: \""You don't get it. They all don't get it. You"
  body " don't understand, man.\"" Daddy's on the '''drink''' again.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=w:Blake Bailey|title='Tennessee Williams,' by John Lahr &#91;print version: Theatrical victory of art over l"
  body "ife, ''International New York Times'', 18 November 2014, p.&nbsp;13&#93;|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/16/books/review/tennessee-williams-by-john-lahr.html|work=w:The New York Times|date=14 Novem"
  body "ber 2014|passage={{...}} she was indeed Amanda in the flesh: a doughty chatterbox from Ohio who adopted the manner of a Southern belle and eschewed both '''drink''' and sex to the greatest extent poss"
  body "ible.}}\n# A [[standard drink]].\n#: {{ux|en|A '''drink''' of wine is about 5 ounces}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1963|title=Vital and Health Statistics: Programs and collection procedures|page=125|text"
  body "=And when (SUBJECT) was 55, would you say (he/she) drank more than, less than, or about 2 to 3 '''drinks''' a day?}}\n# {{lb|en|colloquial|with ''the''}} Any body of water.\n#: {{ux|en|If he doesn't p"
  body "ay off the mafia, he’ll wear cement shoes to the bottom of the '''drink'''!}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|year=1996\n|author=John French+\n|title=A Drop in the Ocean: Dramatic Accounts of Aircrew Saved From th"
  body "e Sea\n|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=lgSSAwAAQBAJ&pg=PT99\n|isbn=9781473813809\n|page=99\n|publisher=Pen and Sword\n|1=en\n|passage=When in mid-Channel the speed slowed and I was informed"
  body " by A.C. Russell that another dinghy had been spotted. This turned out to contain a Canadian fighter pilot who had been in the '''drink''' for three days and was in rather a bad way. He said he had se"
  body "en all the aircraft flying over in the two days before D-Day and since, but no one had sighted him.}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|year=2011\n|author=Levi Johnston\n|title=Deer in the Headlights: My Life in Sar"
  body "ah Palin's Crosshairs\n|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=g9eNWzfPx8IC&pg=PT34\n|isbn=9781451651676\n|page=34\n|publisher=Simon and Schuster\n|1=en\n|passage=In seconds, we went from sitting i"
  body "n a boat to threading ice-cold water. I wasn't wearing a life jacket and am not the best paddler, but there I was, in the '''drink''', splashing around.}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|year=2012\n|author=Jack R."
  body " Myers\n|title=Shot at and Missed: Recollections of a World War II Bombardier\n|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=93PZi5CSZ0AC&pg=PT31\n|isbn=9780806184890\n|page=31\n|publisher=University of "
  body "Oklahoma Press\n|1=en\n|passage=If the planes couldn't make it, they would go in the '''drink''', eject their rubber lifeboats, inflate them, climb in, and pray for the Navy to pick them up before the"
  body " Germans did.}}\n# {{lb|en|Australia|figurative}} A [[downpour]]; a [[cloudburst]]; a [[rainstorm]]; a [[deluge]]; a lot of [[rain]].\n#* {{quote-av|en|speaker=Nate Byrne|title=[[:w:News Breakfast|New"
  body "s Breakfast]]|season=2023|number=74|publisher=[[:w:ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]]|date=13 April 2023|at=07:56 am (UTC+10/AEST)|location=Melbourne, Australia|text=Now this is going to bring some huge "
  body "totals of rainfall with it—200 to 400 millimetres with it—and along with that, these winds—gusts to 275 kilometres an hour near the cyclone &#91;[[:w:Cyclone Ilsa|Cyclone Ilsa]]&#93; core—and that's a"
  body " real concern. That's very destructive winds and it's going to carry this inertia and the rain with it well inland. And we're likely going to be talking about a cyclone all the way through Friday as i"
  body "t slowly weakens, eventually washing that moisture out into a front going through the south. It means the southeast is getting a '''drink''' but [[Western Australia|W.A.]]'s northwest really copping i"
  body "t, individual totals significantly higher than what you're seeing here [on the weather map].}}\n# {{lb|en|informal}} {{1|amount}}.\n#* {{quote-video game|en|year=2004|title=w:Paper Mario: The Thousand"
  body "-Year Door|developer=Intelligent Systems|publisher=Nintendo|system=GameCube|level=|translator=Nintendo of America|text=He [a sea-serpent] was giant, massive. A huge '''drink''' of man-eater. But even "
  body "now, you know, I could take him.}}\n\n=====Usage notes=====\n* A plainer term than more elevated {{m|en|beverage}}. '''Beverage''' is of French origin, while ''drink'' is of Old English origin, and th"
  body "is stylistic difference by origin is common; see {{w|list of English words with dual French and Anglo-Saxon variations}}.\n* In the sense of ''any body of water'' the term is often associated with (a "
  body "threat of) [[drowning]].\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{sense|served beverage}} ''See'' [[Thesaurus:beverage]]\n* {{sense|alcoholic beverage, served or in general}} ''See'' [[Thesaurus:alcoholic beverage]"
  body "]\n* {{sense|action of drinking}} {{l|en|gulp}}, {{l|en|sip}}, {{l|en|swig}}\n* {{sense|type of beverage}} {{l|en|beverage}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col4|en|title=Terms derived from ''drink'' (n"
  body "oun)|antidrink|cooldrink|drinkery|drinkfest|drinkie|drinkless|drinkmaking|drinkologist|drinkometer|drinksie|drinkstuff|Drinkwater|drinkwater|drinkworthy|interdrink|drinks waiter|herbal drink|roots dri"
  body "nk\n|the {{l|en|big drink|pos=nickname for various bodies of water}}|drank|drink-driver|drink-driving|drive to drink|in the drink|straw that stirs the drink|take to drink| B-drink|be the worse for dri"
  body "nk|black drink|call drink|can I buy you a drink|drink alert|drink hail|drink link|drink problem|drink run|drink shop|drink table|drink walking|energy drink|fizzy drink|fountain drink|gangly drink of w"
  body "ater|have drink taken|in drink|long drink|long drink of water|meat and drink|mixed drink|pre-drink|rail drink|scrawny drink of water|skinny drink of water|junk drink|soft drink|sports drink|standard d"
  body "rink|strong drink|Swedish drink|tall drink of water|top-heavy with drink|well drink| drinks cabinet|drinks o'clock|drinks table|pre-drinks|the drinks are on me|cold drink money|functional drink|hold o"
  body "ne's drink|orange drink|dew-drink|drinks trolley|red drink|predrinks|short drink|medium drink|hard drink|tall drink|table drink}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{top3}}\n* {{desc|tpi|dring}}\n* {{desc|cs|"
  body "drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|da|drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|nl|drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fi|drinkki|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fr|drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|de|Drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|it|drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ja|ドリンク|tr=d"
  body "orinku|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pl|drink|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|pt|drinque|drink}}\n* {{desc|sv|drink|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top-see|served beverage|beverage}}\n{{multitrans|"
  body "data=\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|drank}}, {{tt|af|drankie}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|pije|f}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{t|alt|суузун}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|شَرَاب|m}}, {{t|ar|مَشْرُوب|m}}\n*: Hijazi Arab"
  body "ic: {{t|acw|مَشْرُوب|m|tr=mašrūb}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|խմիչք}}\n* Aromanian: {{tt|rup|biuturã|f}}\n* Asturian: {{tt+|ast|bebida|f}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|içki}}\n* Bashkir: {{tt|ba|эсемлек}}\n* B"
  body "asque: {{tt+|eu|edan}}, {{tt+|eu|edari}}, {{tt+|eu|edateko}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|напо́й|m}}\n* Belizean Creole: {{tt|bzj|jrink}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|died|f}}, {{tt+|br|evaj|m}}, {{tt+|br|boeson|m}}"
  body "\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|питие́|n}}, {{tt+|bg|напи́тка|f}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|ယမကာ}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|beguda|f}}, {{tt+|ca|glop|m}}\n* Cebuano: {{tt|ceb|imnunon}}\n* Chamicuro: {{tt|ccc|lajpa'sac"
