  body "{{tt+|hu|ital}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|jooma}}\n* Irish: {{tt+|ga|deoch|f}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|飲料|tr=いんりょう, in'ryō}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|potio|f}}, {{tt|la|potus|m}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|lv|dzēriens|m}}\n* "
  body "Macedonian: {{tt|mk|пијалок|m}}, {{tt|mk|пијачка|f}}\n* Malayalam: {{tt+|ml|പാനീയം}}\n* Marathi: {{tt+|mr|पेय}}\n* Old English: {{tt|ang|drenc|m}}, {{tt|ang|wǣt|n}}\n* Persian: {{tt+|fa|نوشابه|tr=nôšâ"
  body "ba}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{tt|pdt|Drunk|m}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|napój|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|bebida|f}}, {{tt+|pt|coquetel|m}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|напи́ток|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt"
  body "|sh|напитак|m}}, {{tt|sh|пиће|n}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|napitak|m}}, {{tt+|sh|piće|n}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|bebida|f}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|kinywaji}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|dryck|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|"
  body "inumin}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|içecek}}, {{tt+|tr|meşrubat}} {{qualifier|without alcohol}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|شربت|tr=şerbet}}, {{t|ota|شراب|tr=şarab}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|đồ uống}}, {{tt"
  body "+|vi|thức uống}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top-see|served alcoholic beverage|shot}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt|af|drankie}}, {{tt+|af|dop}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|խմիչք}}\n* Asturian: {{tt+|ast|bebida|f}}\n"
  body "* Basque: {{tt+|eu|edan}}, {{tt+|eu|edari}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|evaj|m}}, {{tt+|br|boeson|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|питие́|n}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|beguda|f}}, {{tt+|ca|glop|m}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|к"
  body "ъаьрка}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|drink|m}}, {{tt+|cs|pití|n}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|drink}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|drank|m}}, {{tt+|nl|drinken}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|drinkaĵo}}, {{tt|eo|alkoholaĵo}}\n* Estonian"
  body ": {{tt+|et|jook}}, {{tt+|et|drink}}\n* Ewe: {{tt|ee|aha|n}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|juoma}}, {{tt+|fi|drinkki}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|verre|m}}\n* Georgian: {{tt+|ka|სასმელი}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Getränk|n"
  body "}}, {{q|specifically}} {{tt|de|[[alkoholisch|alkoholisches]] [[Getränk]]}}, {{q|chiefly ones containing liquor also}} {{tt+|de|Drink|m}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|ποτό|n}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|מַשְׁקֶה|m|tr=m"
  body "ashké}}, {{t+|he|מַשְׁקֶה חָרִיף|m|tr=mashké kharíf}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|ital}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt+|is|drykkur|m}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|minuman keras}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|jooma}}\n* Italian: {"
  body "{tt+|it|bevanda|f}}, {{tt|it|[[bevanda]] [[alcolica]]}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|お酒|tr=おさけ, osake}}\n* Jeju: {{t|jje|술}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|술}}, {{tt+|ko|약주}} {{qualifier|honorific}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|p"
  body "otus|m}}, {{tt|la|potio|f}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|lv|dzēriens|m}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt+|lt|gėrimas|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|пијалок|m}}, {{tt|mk|пијачка|f}}\n* Mongolian: {{tt+|mn|архи}}\n* Norman: {{tt|n"
  body "rf|béthe|m}}, {{tt|nrf|bouaisson|f}}, {{tt|nrf|brévage|m}}\n* Ojibwe: {{tt|oj|minikwewin}}\n* Old English: {{tt|ang|drenc|m}}, {{tt|ang|līþ|n}}\n* Persian: {{tt+|fa|مشروب|tr=mašrub}}, {{tt+|fa|باده|tr"
  body "=bâda}}, {{tt|fa|درینک|tr=drink}}, {{tt|fa|نوشیدنی الکلی|tr=nôšidaniye alkoli}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|drink|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|bebida|f}}, {{tt+|pt|drinque|m}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|băutură|f}}"
  body "\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|напи́ток|m}}, {{tt+|ru|вы́пивка|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|пиће|n}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|piće|n}}\n* Slovene: {{tt+|sl|pijača|f}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|trago|m}},"
  body " {{tt+|es|copa|f}}, {{tt|es|alipús|m}}, {{t+|es|drink|m}} {{qualifier|Americas}}, {{t|es|drinque|m}} {{qualifier|Caribbean}}, {{t|es|plosh|m}} {{qualifier|El Salvador}}, {{t|es|tictacazo|m}} {{qualifi"
  body "er|El Salvador}}, {{t|es|bajapanti|m}} {{q|strong|Panama}}, {{t|es|triquis|m}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|drink|c}}, {{tt+|sv|dricka}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|inumin}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|పానీయం}}\n* Thai: {{t-"
  body "needed|th}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|alkollü içecek}}, {{tt+|tr|içki}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t-check|vi|[[ly]] [[rượu]]}}{{attn|vi|was \""[[ly]] [[rượu]]\""}}, {{t-check|vi|[[cốc]] [[rượu]]}}{{attn|vi|was \""[[cố"
  body "c]] rượu\"" - assumed sum-of-parts; if an idiom, use <nowiki>{{t}}</nowiki> instead of <nowiki>{{t-SOP}}</nowiki>. see [[User:Kephir/gadgets/xte#Translation_fixing]]}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|ọtí}}\n{{trans-"
  body "bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|action of drinking}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|drink}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|пиене|n}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|мала}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|pití|n}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|tår|c}}\n* Dutch"
  body ": {{tt+|nl|drinken|n}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|trinko}}\n* Estonian: {{tt|et|joomine}}, {{tt|et|jooming}}\n* Ewe: {{tt|ee|nunono|n}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|kulaus}}, {{tt+|fi|siemaus}}, {{tt+|fi|hörppy}}\"
  body "n* French: {{tt+|fr|boire}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|bebida|f}}\n* Georgian: {{tt|ka|სმა}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Trinken|n}}, {{tt+|de|Trinkerei|f}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|πόση|f}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{tt|grc|"
  body "πόσις|f}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|שתייה|alt=שְׁתִיָּה|tr=shtiyá|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|ivás}}\n* Irish: {{tt+|ga|deoch|f}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|bevuta|f}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|飲用|tr=いんよう, in'yō}}\n* "
  body "Latin: {{tt|la|potio|f}}, {{tt|la|potus|m}}, {{tt|la|bibitiō|f}} {{q|Medieval}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|lv|malks|m}}, {{tt|lv|dzeršana|f}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt+|lt|gėrimas|f}}, {{tt+|lt|išgėrimas|m}}\n* Marat"
  body "hi: {{t-check|mr|पिणे}}, {{t+check|mr|पान}}, {{t-check|mr|[[पिण्याची]] [[क्रिया]]}}{{attn|mr|was \""पिण्याची क्रिया\"" - not sure how it is supposed to be linked}}\n* Neapolitan: {{tt|nap|véppata}}\n* O"
  body "ld English: {{tt|ang|drync|m}}\n* Persian: {{tt+|fa|نوشیدن|tr=nôšidan}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|picie|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|bebida|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|питьё|n}}\n* Sami:\n*: Kildin Sami: {{t|sj"
  body "d|югкмушш}}\n* Slovene: {{tt|sl|požirek|m}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|beber|m}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|nywa|alt=kunywa}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|drickande|n}}, {{tt+|sv|klunk|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|pag-inom}}\"
  body "n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|içmek}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|uống}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|alcoholic beverages in general}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|drank}}, {{tt+|af|dop}}\n* Arabic:\n*: Moroccan Ara"
  body "bic: {{tt|ary|شراب|tr=šrāb}}\n* Basque: {{tt+|eu|alkohol}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|алкохолни напитки|p}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|къаьрка}}, {{tt|ce|алкоголин малар}}, {{tt|ce|спирт}}, {{tt|ce|корта бахош до"
  body "лу малар}}, {{tt|ce|алкоголь}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|alkohol}}, {{tt|da|spiritus}}\n* Ewe: {{tt|ee|aha|n}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|alkoholijuoma}}\n* Georgian: {{t-needed|ka}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Drink|m}}"
  body "\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|ποτό|n}}, {{tt+|el|οινοπνευματώδη|n-p}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|מַשְׁקָאוֹת חָרִיפִים|m-p|tr=mashka'ót kharifím}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|szeszes ital}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|酒|tr=さけ, sak"
  body "e}}, {{tt+|ja|お酒|tr=おさけ, osake}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|potus|m}}, {{tt|la|potio|f}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|пијалок|m}}, {{tt|mk|пијачка|f}}\n* Marathi: {{tt|mr|अपेयपेय}}, {{tt|mr|दारू}}, {{tt|mr|मदिरा}}\n"
  body "* Persian: {{tt+|fa|می|tr=may}}, {{tt+|fa|مشروب|tr=mašrôb}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|trunki|p}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|bebida|f}}, {{tt+|pt|álcool|m}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|вы́пивка|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\"
  body "n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|пиће|n}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|piće|n}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|alipús|m}}, {{t|es|chínguere|m}} {{qualifier|Mexico}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|dricka}}, {{tt+|sv|sprit}}, {{tt+|sv|alkohol}}"
  body "\n* Thai: {{t-needed|th}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|rượu}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|\""the drink\""- colloquially, any body of water}}\n* Latin: {{tt|la|potus|m}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|dricka|n}}, "
  body "{{tt+|sv|spad|n}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Breton: {{t+check|br|died|f}}, {{t+check|br|evaj|m}}\n* German:\n*: Old High German: {{t-check|goh|trunch}"
  body "}\n* Guarani:\n*: Paraguayan Guarani: {{t-check|gug|jey'urã}}\n* Interlingua: {{t-check|ia|bibita}}, {{t-check|ia|biberage}}\n* Low German: {{t+check|nds|drinken|n}}\n* Old English: {{t-check|ang|dryn"
  body "c}}\n* Old Norse: {{t-check|non|drykkr|m}}\n* Thai: {{t+check|th|เหล้า|tr=lao}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{cln|en|strong verbs|irregular verbs}}\n{{C|en|Food and drink|Liquids|Units of measure}}\n{{cln|en"
  body "|autohyponyms}}<!-- drink any liquid vs. drink alcohol -->\n\n==Afrikaans==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|af|nl|drinken}}, from {{inh|af|dum|drinken}}, from {{inh|af|odt|drinkan}}, from {{inh|af|gem-"
  body "pro|*drinkaną}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|af|LL-Q14196 (afr)-Iwan.Aucamp-drink.wav}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{af-verb}}\n\n# to [[#English|drink]]\n\n==Czech==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|cs|:bor|en"
  body ":drink<id:noun>}}\n{{bor+|cs|en|drink}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{cs-IPA}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{cs-noun|m-in}}\n\n# {{l|en|drink}} {{gloss|a (mixed) alcoholic beverage}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{cs-nde"
  body "cl|m}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:cs:PSJC}}\n* {{R:cs:SSJC}}\n\n{{C|cs|Alcoholic beverages}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|da|:bor|en:drink<id:noun>}}\nFrom {{bor|da|en|drink}}.\n\n="
  body "==Noun===\n{{da-noun|en|s}}\n\n# {{l|en|drink}}; a (mixed) alcoholic beverage\n\n====Inflection====\n{{da-noun-infl|en|drinks|drinksene|||drinks'}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|da|sjus|g=c}}\n\n===Furth"
  body "er reading===\n* {{R:DDO}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/drɪŋk/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-drink.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|drink}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|ɪŋk|s=1}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|nl"
  body "|:bor|en:drink<id:noun>}}\nBorrowed from {{bor|nl|en|drink}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|m|-s|-}}\n\n# {{lb|nl|Belgium}} a social event were [[beverage]]s are served, with or without snacks, e.g. as a"
  body " celebration\n# {{lb|nl|Netherlands}} a [[beverage]], a {{l|en|drink}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|nl|verb form}}\n\n# {{infl of|nl|drinken||bare-verb}}\n\n==French==\n\"
  body "n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:bor|en:drink<id:noun>}}\n{{bor+|fr|en|drink}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|dring_k}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Lyokoï-drink.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n\n===Nou"
  body "n===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# a [[reception]] or [[after-party|afterparty]] where alcohol is served\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|it|:ubor|en:drink<i"
  body "d:noun>}}\n{{ubor|it|en|drink}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr|^ì<r:DiPI>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|m|#,drinks<l:dated>}}\n\n# {{l|en|drink}} {{gloss|served beverage and mixed beverage}}\n#: {{syn|"
  body "it|bevanda}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|it\n|year=1970\n|tlr=Mercedes Giardini\n|title=Il padrino\n|original={{w|The Godfather (novel)|The Godfather}}\n|by=w:Mario Puzo\n|publisher=dall'Oglio editore\n|locati"
  body "on=Milan\n|chapter=Ⅻ\n|page=160\n|text=«Non sono in forma con la voce», rispose. «E con tutta sincerità, sono stufo di sentirmi cantare». Sorseggiarono i '''drinks'''.\n|t=\""My voice is not doing well"
  body "\"", he replied. \""And, in all honesty, I'm tired of hearing myself singing\"". They sipped their '''drinks'''.\n}}\n#* {{quote-av\n|it\n|title=La grande bellezza\n|role=Jep Gambardella\n|actor=Toni Ser"
  body "villo\n|writer=w:Paolo Sorrentino\n|year=2013\n|time=01:39:42\n|passage=Io berrò molti '''drink''', ma non così tanti da diventare molesto.\n|t=I'll drink many '''drinks''', but not so many to become "
  body "annoying.}}\n\n===References===\n{{reflist}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:it:Trec}}\n\n==Low German==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|nds|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|nds|drinken||1|s}}\n\n==North Frisia"
  body "n==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|frr|drank||Föhr-Amrum}}\n* {{alt|frr|drinke||Halligen}}\n* {{alt|frr|drainke||Mooring}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|frr|ofs|drinka}}, from {{inh|frr|gmw-pro|"
  body "*drinkan}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|frr|[d̥rɪŋk]|a=Sylt}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|frr|verb|present}}\n\n# {{lb|frr|Sylt|Heligolandic}} to {{l|en|drink}}\n\n====Conjugation====\n{{frr-Sylt-conj-t"
  body "able|inf_2=drinken|ppp=drunken|pres_2=drinkst|pres_3=drinkt|past_1=droonk|past_2=droonkst}}\n\n==Polish==\n{{wp|pl:}}\n[[File:Margarita.jpg|thumb|drink]]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|pl|:bor|en:drink<id:"
  body "noun>|text=+|tree=1}} {{dbt|pl|dręk|trunek}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|a=Pl-drink.ogg}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|m-anml}}\n\n# [[cocktail]], {{l|en|drink}} {{gl|served alcoholic beverage}}\n#* "
  body "{{quote-song|pl|year=2011|artist=Poparzeni Kawą Trzy|title=Kawałek do tańca|passage=Jeszcze trochę do północy<br/>'''drink''' jak zagubiony pocisk<br/>strzelił mocno mi do głowy<br/>coraz trudniej się"
  body " wysłowić.|t=There's still some time before midnight<br/>The '''drink''', like a lost bullet,<br/>shot me right in the head<br/>it's getting harder and harder to speak.}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{pl-d"
  body "ecl-noun-m-anml}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|pl|title=verbs|drinkować<g:impf>}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:WSJP}}\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n\n{{C|pl|Cocktails}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Etymology=="
  body "=\n{{ubor|pt|en|drink}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA|drinque}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pt-noun|m|#s}}\n\n# {{alternative form of|pt|drinque}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Aulete}}\n* {{R:pt:Priber"
  body "am}}\n\n==Swedish==\n{{wp|sv:}}\n[[File:Dry Martini-2.jpg|thumb|250px|en drink ({{l|sv|cocktail}})]]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|sv|:bor|en:drink<id:noun>}}\nFrom {{bor|sv|en|drink}}. {{doublet|sv|dr"
  body "yck}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sv|/drɪŋk/}}\n* {{audio|sv|Sv-en drink.ogg|a=Gotland}}\n* {{rhymes|sv|ɪŋk|s=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|c}}\n\n# a {{l|en|drink}} ((mixed) alcoholic beverage)\n"
  body "#: {{ux|sv|ta en '''drink'''|enjoy a '''drink'''}}\n#* {{quote-song|sv|year=2021|author=w:Hooja|title=Banan, Melon, Kiwi & Citron|text=Banan, melon, kiwi och citron / De häller det i '''drinken''' och"
  body " säger \""den är god\""|t=Banana, melon, kiwi and lemon / They pour it in '''the drink''' and tell you \""it's good\""}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n''Drink'' in the more general sense of ''beverage'' is {{m|"
  body "sv|dryck}}.\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-infl-noun-c-ar}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|sv\n|drinkare\n|drinkblandare\n|drinklista\n|drinkpinne\n|drinktilltugg\n|fördrink\n|kaffedrink\n|mjölkdrink\n|"
  body "paraplydrink\n|proteindrink\n|softdrink\n|stilldrink\n|välkomstdrink\n}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|sv|dryck}}\n* {{l|sv|grogg}}\n* {{l|sv|sup}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:svenska.se|so}}\n* {{R:svens"
  body "ka.se|saol}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saob}}\n\n{{C|sv|Alcoholic beverages}}\n\n==West Frisian==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|fy|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|fy|drinke||1|s|pres}}\n# {{inflection of|fy|drinke||"
  body "imp}}\n\n==Yola==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|yol|:inh|enm:drinken}}\nFrom {{inh|yol|enm|drinken}}, from {{inh|yol|ang|drincan}}, from {{inh|yol|gmw-pro|*drinkan}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|yo"
  body "l|/drɪŋk/}}\n* {{IPA|yol|[ˈd̪rɪnkən]<ref:{{R:Muirithe 1990|page=150}}>}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|yol|verb}}\n\n# to {{l|en|drink}}\n#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|chapter=THE WEDDEEN O BALLYMORE|number=4"
  body "|page=96<ref>{{R:Poole 1867|page=96}}</ref>|title=SONGS, ETC. IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage='''Drink''' a heall to a breede. \""Shud with, a voorneen.\""|translation='''Drink''' a health to "
  body "the bride, \""Here's to you, my dear.\""}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|yol|noun}}\n\n# {{l|en|drink}}\n#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|chapter=VERSES IN ANSWER TO THE WEDDEEN O BALLYMORE|page=98|title=SONGS, ET"
  body "C. IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage=Tibbès an crockès wee '''drink''' war ee-felt.|translation=[Tubs and crocks were filled with '''drink'''.]}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>""}}"

