response_0019_api_php_action_parse_pag
  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=hello&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""hello"",""pageid"":4803,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""{{also|helló}}\n\n==English==\n{{phrasebook|en|Greetings}}\n{{was wotd|2007|November|19}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|hall"
  body "o||UK|_|old style}}\n* {{alt|en|hilloa||obsolete}}\n* {{alt|en|hullo||UK}}\n\n===Etymology===\n''Hello'' (first attested in 1826), from {{m|en|holla}}, {{m|en|hollo}} (attested 1588). This variant of "
  body "{{m|en|hallo}} is often credited to [[w:Thomas Edison|Thomas Edison]] as a coinage for telephone use, but its appearance in print predates the invention of the telephone by several decades.\n\nUltimat"
  body "ely from a variant of Old English {{m|ang|ēalā}}, such as {{m|ang|hēlā}}, which was used colloquially at the time similarly to how ''hey'' and (in some dialects) ''hi'' are used nowadays. Thus, equiva"
  body "lent to a compound of {{m|en|hey}} and {{m|en|lo}}. Used when drawing attention to yourself.\n\nPossibly influenced by {{ncog|osx|halo|halo!}}, imperative of {{m|osx|halōn|t=to call, fetch}}, used in "
  body "hailing a ferryman, akin to {{ncog|goh|hala}}, {{m|goh|hola|hola!}}, imperative forms of {{m|goh|halōn}}, {{m|goh|holōn|t=to fetch}}. More at {{l|en|hallo}}.\n\nOED and Merriam-Webster also suggested "
  body "that it is a variant of {{m|en|holla}}, a variant of {{m|en|holloo}}. Further beyond, the origin remains uncertain. OED and Merriam-Webster suggested that it has a connection between {{m|en|hallow|t= "
  body "to shout, to cry out loud}}, which came from Old French {{m|fro|holloer}}, which, according to ''Altfranzösisches Wörterbuch'', is from {{cog|osx|halōn}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/hɛˈloʊ/|/"
  body "həˈloʊ/|/ˈhɛloʊ/|a=GA}}, {{enPR|hĕ-lō'|hə-lō'}}\n* {{a|en|UK}}\n** {{IPA|en|/həˈləʊ/|/hɛˈləʊ/|a=RP}}\n** {{IPA|en|/hæˈlaʊ/|a=Northumbrian}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-hello.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{IPA|en|/həˈləʉ/|a"
  body "=AU}}\n** {{audio|en|En-au-hello.ogg|a=AU}}\n* {{IPA|en|/hɛˈloː/|/həˈloː/|/ˈhɛloː/|/ˈhɛlo/|a=CA}}\n* {{IPA|en|/həˈlo(w)/|a=Indic}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɛləʊ|s=2}}\n{|class=\""wikitable\""\n! Sense\n! UK\n! US"
  body "\n|-\n|{{sense|greeting}}\n|{{audio|en|en-uk-hello-1.ogg|a=UK}}\n|{{audio|en|en-us-hello.ogg|a=US}}\n|-\n|{{sense|telephone greeting}}\n|{{audio|en|en-uk-hello-2.ogg|a=UK}}\n|{{audio|en|en-us-hello-2."
  body "ogg|a=US}}\n|-\n|{{sense|call for response}}\n|{{audio|en|en-uk-hello-3.ogg|a=UK}}\n|{{audio|en|en-us-hello-3.ogg|a=US}}\n|-\n|{{sense|sarcastic implication}}\n|{{audio|en|en-uk-hello-4.ogg|a=UK}}\n|{"
  body "{audio|en|en-us-hello-4.ogg|a=US}}\n|-\n|{{sense|expressing puzzlement}}\n|{{audio|en|en-uk-hello-5.ogg|a=UK}}\n|\n|}\n* {{rhymes|en|əʊ|s=2}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# {{ng|A [[greeting]"
  body "] ([[salutation]]) said when [[meet]]ing someone or [[acknowledge|acknowledging]] someone’s [[arrival]] or [[presence]].}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Hello''', everyone.}}\n# {{ng|A greeting used when [[answer]]i"
  body "ng the [[telephone]].}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Hello'''? How may I help you?}}\n#* '''2016''', [https://web.archive.org/web/20170918070146/https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/lets-learn-english-lesson-3-i-a"
  body "m-here/3126527.html VOA Learning English] (public domain)\n#*: '''Hello'''. This is Marsha. ― Yes, Marsha.\n# {{ng|A call for [[response]] if it is not clear if anyone is present or listening, or if a"
  body " telephone conversation may have been [[disconnect]]ed.}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Hello'''? Is anyone there?}}\n#* {{RQ:Lincoln Pratt's Patients|chapter=7|passage=I made a speaking trumpet of my hands and comm"
  body "enced to whoop “Ahoy!” and “'''Hello!'''” at the top of my lungs. {{...}} The Colonel woke up, and, after asking what in brimstone was the matter, opened his mouth and roared “Hi!” and “'''Hello!'''” "
  body "like the bull of Bashan.}}\n# {{lb|en|colloquial}} {{ng|Used [[sarcastic]]ally to imply that the person addressed has done something the speaker considers to be [[foolish]], or missed something that s"
  body "hould have been [[obvious]].}}\n#: {{ux|en|You just tried to start your car with your cell phone. '''Hello'''?}}\n#* {{quote-video game|en|year=2004|title=w:Paper Mario: The Thousand-Year Door|develop"
  body "er=Intelligent Systems|publisher=Nintendo|system=GameCube|level=Rogueport|translator=Nintendo of America|text=Uh, '''hello'''? We're using a CANNON to get to the moon? Isn't that, like, dangerous?}}\n"
  body "# {{lb|en|chiefly|UK}} {{ng|An expression of [[puzzlement]] or [[discovery]].}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Hello'''! What’s going on here?}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* The greeting {{m|en|hello}} is among the most"
  body " universal and neutral in use. It may be heard in nearly all social situations and nearly all walks of life and is unlikely to offend.\n\n*In the derived  senses, the word-final stress may be emphasiz"
  body "ed to focus attention, but word-initial stress is also heard in certain contexts, such as some uses of {{m|en|hello there}}, and even in isolation.\n\n====Quotations====\n* {{see citations|en}}\n\n==="
  body "=Synonyms====\n* {{sense|greeting}} {{see thesaurus|en|hello}}\n** {{qualifier|Australia, informal}} [[g'day]], [[hey]], [[hi]]\n** {{qualifier|UK, informal}} [[hallo]], [[hi]], [[hiya]], [[ey up]], ["
  body "[you alright]], [[alright]]\n** {{qualifier|US, informal}} [[hallo]], [[hey]], [[hi]], [[howdy]]\n** {{qualifier|Ireland, informal}} [[how's it going]], [[hey]], [[hi]]\n** {{qualifier|South Africa, i"
  body "nformal}} [[howzit]]\n** {{qualifier|slang}} [[wassup]], [[what's up]], [[yo]], [[sup]], [[what's good]]\n* {{sense|expression of puzzlement}} {{see thesaurus|en|wow}}\n\n====Antonyms====\n* {{antsens"
  body "e|greeting}} {{l|en|bye}}, {{l|en|goodbye}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|golden hello\n|hello again\n|hello girl\n|helloji\n|hello nurse\n|hello there|say hello\n|Hello World\n|hello yourself, a"
  body "nd see how you like it\n|yello\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|hy|հէլօ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|am|ሀሎ|tr=halo|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|zh|哈嘍|哈囉|哈佬|tr3=hālǎo|哈咯|ciallo|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ja|ハロー|tr=harō|bor=1}}\n"
  body "* {{desc|ms|helo|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|gd|halò|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|cy|helo|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|acm|هلو|bor=1}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|greeting}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Abaza: {{tt|abq|сальам}}\n* "
  body "Abkhaz: {{tt|ab|бзиа збаша}}, {{tt|ab|мыш бзи}}, {{qualifier|to a man}} {{tt|ab|бзиара убааит}}, {{qualifier|to a woman}} {{tt|ab|бзиара ббааит}}, {{qualifier|to more than one person}} {{tt|ab|бзиара "
  body "жәбааит|p}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|hallo}}, {{t|af|goeiedag}}\n* Ahom: {{tt|aho|𑜈𑜩𑜨 𑜀𑜪𑜨}}\n* Ainu: {{tt|ain|イランカラㇷ゚テ|tr=irankarapte}}\n* Akan: {{t|ak|maakye}} {{qualifier|morning}}, {{t|ak|maaha}} {{q"
  body "ualifier|afternoon}}, {{t|ak|maadwo}} {{qualifier|evening}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|përshëndetje}}, {{tt+|sq|tungjatjeta}}, {{tt|sq|tung}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{tt|sq|ç'kemi|m|f}}\n*: Arbëresh Alban"
  body "ian: {{t+|aae|falem}}\n* Aleut: {{tt|ale|aang}}, {{tt|ale|draas}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{t|alt|эзен}}, {{t|alt|селем}}\n* Alutiiq: {{t|ems|cama’i}}\n* Ambonese Malay: {{tt|abs|wai}}\n* Americ"
  body "an Sign Language: {{tt|ase|B@Sfhead-PalmForward B@FromSfhead-PalmForward}}\n* Amharic: {{tt|am|ሰላም}}\n* Apache:\n*: Jicarilla: {{tt|apj|dá nzhǫ́}}\n*: Western Apache: {{tt|apw|dagotʼee}}, {{tt|apw|daʼ"
  body "anzho}}, {{tt|apw|yaʼateh}}\n* Arabic: {{tt+|ar|السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكُمْ}}, {{tt+|ar|سَلَام}}, {{tt+|ar|مَرْحَبًا}}, {{tt+|ar|أَهْلًا}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|اهلاً|tr=ahlan}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {"
  body "{t|acw|مَرحَبا|tr=marḥaba}}, {{t|acw|هلا|tr=hala}}, {{t|acw|السلام عليكم|tr=as-salāmu ʕalēkum}}, {{t|acw|أهلًا|tr=ʔahlan}}\n*: Iraqi Arabic: {{tt|acm|هلو|tr=helaww}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Arama"
  body "ic: {{t|aii|ܫܠܵܡܵܐ}}, {{t|aii|ܫܠܵܡܵܐ ܥܲܠܘܼܟ݂}} {{q|formal; to a male}}, {{t|aii|ܫܠܵܡܵܐ ܥܲܠܵܟ݂ܝ}} {{q|formal; to a female}}, {{t|aii|ܫܠܵܡܵܐ ܥܲܠܵܘܟ݂ܘܿܢ}} {{q|formal; to a group}}\n* Archi: {{tt|aqc|сала"
